# Plugin Development Guidelines

## Plugin File Structure
- Each plugin gets its own file in [lua/plugins/](mdc:lua/plugins/)
- File naming: lowercase, hyphenated (e.g., `treesitter.lua`, `git-stuff.lua`)
- Return Lazy configuration table from each plugin file

## Plugin Configuration Patterns
- Use consistent table structure for Lazy specs
- Include proper dependencies and requirements
- Set appropriate lazy loading conditions
- Configure plugin-specific options clearly

## Key Mapping Integration
- Add plugin-specific keymaps in the plugin file when possible
- Use descriptive keymap descriptions
- Follow existing patterns from [remap.lua](mdc:lua/remap.lua)
- Test keymaps for conflicts with existing mappings

## LSP and Language Support
- Configure language servers in [lua/plugins/lsp.lua](mdc:lua/plugins/lsp.lua)
- Use Mason for LSP installation and management
- Configure formatters via none-ls integration
- Test language-specific features thoroughly

## Plugin Dependencies
- Declare dependencies clearly in Lazy configuration
- Use version pinning for critical plugins
- Test plugin interactions and conflicts
- Document any special setup requirements